                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/2351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Arica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Von Tresckow</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-05-27T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 27, 1926—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Lassiter. Your telegram May 26, 10 p.m. Please continue to send in reports as
                    detailed as possible covering all incidents such as you have reported. Mr.
                    Stimson and Mr. Dennis<note n="3" xml:id="d300fn3">William C. Dennis, formerly
                        at Arica as general legal adviser to the president of the Plebiscitary
                        Commission.</note> are working continuously on this matter; early next week
                    they expect to be able to make a complete report based on all data available
                    here. We all appreciate fully the difficulties and embarrassments of your
                    position as well as the dangers which are inherent in the local situation and at
                    earliest possible moment I shall give you decisions on policy. Please rest
                    assured that all phases of the problem are receiving most earnest and active
                    attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
